(Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Tunis - At least 14 people were killed and 70 injured when a passenger train hit a lorry south of the Tunisian capital on Tuesday, the transport and interior ministries said.Most of the dead were passengers on the train, which derailed, the transport ministry said. Both drivers were also killed.The interior ministry said the train was heading into the capital from the town of Gaafour, 120km to the southwest, in the morning rush hour.The collision happened near El Fahes, some 60km from Tunis, at around 06:30."The death toll could rise," Transport Minister Mahmoud Ben Romdhane told Mosaique FM radio.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.